description:
Alternative AI with improvements over the original: 
1- AI now rebuilds destroyed walls and will create Town Centers on islands; 
2- Prioritize reaching the maximum number of military units; 
3 - Reduction in the resource bonus applied to AI at higher levels to make games more balanced; 
4 - Improvement in the frequency of attacks to reduce the number of AI suicide waves;
5 - Significant improvements in the use of God Powers and the logic of unit and building upgrades, especially mid game.

Additive mod that adds lot of new technologies focused around military, including few new techs exclusive for every faction/nation. The biggest focus of added tech was to make the heroes a bit more "heroic" in the late game (especially by making the greek heroes more even in their power-level), as well as help the more favor-struggling factions to gather it faster (at a cost).

You can find new tech at:
- Settlement/Citadel;
- Fortress/Migdol/Fort/Palace/Baolei/Castle;
- Armory/Dwarven Armory;
- Temple;
- Monument to gods;
- Oracle;
- Hersir/Godi;
- Miko;
- Counter Barracks;
- Imperial Academy;
- Dock;

Additive mod that adds over dozen new technologies focused around defensive capabilities of your structures.      
The forts are now further distiguished from towers by having higher damage at a cost of reduced RoF, however HP remainds unchanged.      
Besides that the mod adds buildable mirror towers to every god (faction), making them avaiable from heroic age. The mirror towers are now longer range defensive alternative that deals rather medicore damage with very slow RoF, however does a chain attack and bonus damage against mythic units and titans.     
     
Mirror towers can be build by:     
- villagers (greece);     
- priests (egypt);     
- hersis/godi (norse);     
- citizens (atleantian);     
- kuafus (chinese);     
- commoners (japenese).

Additive mod that adds a single new mythic age technology to every existing major gods. The tech itself is free in costs, but has longer research time.
The idea of the mod was to further distinguish dimishing in time gameplay differences by focusing on strengths of each of the major gods:
- Zeus - heroes and infantry units;
- Hades - buildings and ranged units;
- Poseidon - economy and cavalry units;
- Ra - pharaoh and migdol units;
- Isis - buildings and temple units;
- Set - cursed animals and barrack units;
- Thor - dwarves and siege units;
- Odin - economy and great hall units;
- Loki - myth and longhouse units;
- Freyr - buildings and heroes;
- Kronos - cavalry and myth units;
- Oranos - oracles and spped;
- Gaia - heroes and buildings;
- Fuxi - heroes and baolei units;
- Nuwa - buildings and imperial academy units;
- Shennong - myth and military camp units;
- Amaterasu - heroes and economy;
- Tsukuyomi - cavalry and dojo units;
- Susanoo - myth and guardhouse units;
